PRIME Minister Kassim Majaliwa has directed local government authorities (LGAs) to allocate business areas to house petty traders. The new market areas, according to PM, should accommodate especially those recently issued with special identity cards introduced by President John Magufuli. “We understand challenges faced entrepreneurs, driving some to shun the petty traders’ identity cards. But we will continue to improve petty traders working environment by meeting with them to discuss challenges they are facing,’’ said Mr Majaliwa. The PM gave the order when addressing a public rally at Ilagala Village in Uvinza District, Kigoma Region. He said government recognises the contribution of small entrepreneurs in raising the country’s economy which is the driving force to improving traders working environment. The issuing of petty traders ID cards will enable the government to have correct data on them to make